  "local_port": 46614,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some things new employees should know going into their first day at Select Medical?",
  "response": "Starting a new job at Select Medical can be an exciting yet nerve-wracking experience. To help new employees prepare for their first day, here are some key things they should know:\n\n1. **Company Culture and Values**: Select Medical places a strong emphasis on its core values, which include integrity, compassion, accountability, respect, and excellence. Understanding and embodying these values can help new employees integrate more seamlessly into the workplace.\n\n2. **Dress Code**: Depending on your role, the dress code may vary. For clinical positions, scrubs or professional attire suitable for patient interaction may be required. For corporate roles, business casual or professional attire is typically expected. It's a good idea to confirm the specific dress code with your hiring manager or HR representative.\n\n3. **Arrival and Check-In**: Plan to arrive a bit early on your first day. You'll need to check in at the designated reception or HR department, where you'll complete any necessary paperwork and receive your employee badge.\n\n4. **Orientation and Training**: Select Medical typically conducts an orientation program for new hires. This may include an overview of the company, its mission, safety protocols, and introductions to key team members. Be prepared to participate actively and take notes.\n\n5. **Technology and Systems**: You may be introduced to various software systems and tools used at Select Medical, such as electronic health records (EHR) for clinical staff or other company-specific platforms. Familiarizing yourself with these systems early on can help you become more efficient in your role.\n\n6. **Team Dynamics and Communication**: Take time to get to know your immediate team and supervisors. Understanding the communication channels and dynamics within your department will be crucial for effective collaboration.\n\n7. **Patient Care Focus**: For those in clinical roles, remember that patient care is at the heart of Select Medical's mission. Being compassionate, attentive, and professional in your interactions with patients is highly valued.\n\n8. **Safety and Compliance**: Select Medical prioritizes safety and compliance with healthcare regulations. Be prepared to learn about and adhere to protocols related to patient safety, infection control, and other relevant standards.\n\n9. **Benefits and HR Support**: You'll likely receive information about your benefits package, including health insurance, retirement plans, and other perks. Don't hesitate to reach out to the HR department if you have questions or need assistance.\n\n10. **Openness to Learning**: Be open to learning and adapting. Your first day is just the beginning of your journey with Select Medical, and showing a willingness to grow and improve will be appreciated.\n\nBy keeping these points in mind, new employees can approach their first day at Select Medical with confidence and a better understanding of what to expect.",
